<dl id="n05039d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n05" href="#n05039d">N05 (VI.B.2)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n05all.htm#n05039d"> 39(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Sing passion</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">During his visits <mark>he would sing with great feeling</mark>, my daughter accompanying him on the piano. Sometimes Fr. O&apos;Reilly, the late Cardinal&apos;s administrator and confessor, would come and join him in a glee. <small> William J. Fitz-Patrick, <a name="BURKE" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#BURKE"><cite title="source">The Life of the Very Rev. Thomas N. Burke</cite></a>, (1885) [passim, e.g.] II, 276</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
